"title": "3236: Holy Spirit, and Scripture",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "3236",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The Holy Spirit inspired the original writing of all the Scriptures, and illumines their meaning to believers.</p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit inspired the writing of Scripture</h2>\n<h3>The Spirit inspired the writers of the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:1-2Sam23:2\">2SA 23:1–23:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:30\">NEH 9:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek2:2\">EZK 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:24-Ezek11:25\">EZK 11:24–11:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic3:8\">MIC 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:12\">ZEC 7:12</a></p>\n<h3>The NT recognises OT writings as inspired by the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:16\">2TI 3:16</a></strong> <em>“God-breathed” means “breathed out by God” rather than “inspired”</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:20-2Pet1:21\">2PE 1:20–1:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:43\">MAT 22:43</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:36\">MRK 12:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:16\">ACT 1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:25\">ACT 4:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:25-Acts28:27\">ACT 28:25–28:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:7-Heb3:11\">HEB 3:7–3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:15-Heb10:17\">HEB 10:15–10:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:11\">1PE 1:11</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit inspired the writers of the NT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:4-Eph3:5\">EPH 3:4–3:5</a></strong> <em>This revelation by the Spirit probably includes the apostles' understanding of the gospel and their preaching as well as the writings of the NT.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:40\">1CO 7:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:7\">REV 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:11\">REV 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:17\">REV 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:29\">REV 2:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:6\">REV 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:13\">REV 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:22\">REV 3:22</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit illumines the meaning of Scripture</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:12-1Cor2:16\">1CO 2:12–2:16</a></strong> <em>“what God has freely given” refers to “God's secret wisdom” (verse 7), the “deep things of God” (verse 10) and the “thoughts of God” (verse 11).</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:26\">JHN 14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:13-John16:15\">JHN 16:13–16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:14-2Cor3:17\">2CO 3:14–3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:8\">HEB 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:20\">1JN 2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:27\">1JN 2:27</a></p>\n<h2>The relationship between the word and the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<h3>The association of God's Spirit and breath with his word(s)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:6\">PSA 33:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:21\">ISA 59:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:34\">JHN 3:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:63\">JHN 6:63</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:17\">EPH 6:17</a> <em>“word” here probably means “the gospel” rather than Scripture as a whole.</em></p>\n<h3>The Spirit is essential for obeying God's law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:29\">ROM 2:29</a></strong> <em>Reliance on the letter of the law alone is useless.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:6\">ROM 7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:6\">2CO 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:2\">GAL 3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:5\">GAL 3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:18\">GAL 5:18</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit enables believers to fulfil the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:4\">ROM 8:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:4-Gal5:5\">GAL 5:4–5:5</a></p>",
